Describe a time you tried to do something but was not very successful
- when it was
- what you tried
- why it was not very successful
- how you felt about it

I’d like to talk about a time when I tried to learn how to play the guitar but didn’t succeed as well as I had hoped. This happened about two years ago when I was a second-year university student.

I was inspired by a girl I saw at an English club who was confidently singing and playing the guitar at the same time. I found it really impressive and wanted to be able to do the same. So, I decided to give it a try. I asked a friend of mine, who was quite skilled at playing the guitar, to teach me, and I also bought a guitar so I could practice regularly.

At the beginning, I was very enthusiastic and spent a lot of time practicing. I even watched online tutorials to improve more quickly. However, as time went on, I began to realize that learning the guitar was much more challenging than I had expected. I struggled to remember different chords and often found it difficult to position my fingers correctly. On top of that, my fingertips became quite sore, which made practicing uncomfortable.

As a result, my motivation gradually faded, and I eventually gave up after about a month. Looking back, I do feel a bit disappointed in myself for not being persistent enough. However, I also see it as a learning experience, and I’m determined to give it another try in the future with a more disciplined approach.
